(3299, 27, '2017-02-11 10:47:11', '2017-02-11 10:47:11', '<p>[{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"In%20order%20for%20any%20device%20to%20communicate%20over%20the%20Internet%2C%20it%20uses%20a%20set%20of%20well%20established%20protocols%20that%20define%20how%20data%20is%20exchanged.%20Out%20of%20these%20protocols%2C%20the%20Internet%20Protocol%20%28IP%29%20is%20the%20only%20one%20that%20every%20single%20device%20communicating%20over%20the%20Internet%20needs%20to%20use.%20The%20IP%20protocol%20defines%20the%20addressing%20mechanism%20that%20can%20identify%20devices%20and%20networks%2C%20and%20can%20therefore%20be%20used%20to%20deliver%20packets%20of%20data%20to%20their%20destinations.\",\"rhsI\":\"\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"Has%20been%20the%20dominant%20version%20of%20the%20IP%20protocol%20since%20the%20early%201980%27s.\",\"rhsI\":\"Started%20to%20be%20deployed%20in%20the%20early%202000%27s\"},{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"Both%20protocols%20define%20the%20format%20of%20the%20packets%20sent%20by%20any%20device.%20both%20define%20a%20header%20that%20is%20attached%20to%20each%20packet%20containing%20information%20to%20assist%20in%20the%20delivery%20of%20the%20packet.%20The%20most%20important%20fields%20of%20the%20header%20are%20the%20addresses%20of%20the%20source%20and%20destination.\",\"rhsI\":\"\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"The%20address%20space%20is%2032%20bits%2C%20providing%20around%204%20billion%20different%20addresses\",\"rhsI\":\"The%20address%20space%20is%20128%20bits%2C%20providing%20a%20much%20larger%20number%20of%20possible%20combinations\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Examples\",\"lhsI\":\"The%20convention%20for%20writing%20the%20addresses%20is%20to%20convert%20every%208%20bits%20to%20decimal.%3Cbr%20/%3Eex%3A%20172.22.12.55\",\"rhsI\":\"The%20convention%20is%20to%20convert%20every%2016%20bits%20to%20hexadecimal.%3Cbr%20/%3EEx%3A%2013FA%3A2004%3A0BAC%3AFEE4%3A%3A%3Cbr%20/%3Econsecutive%20colons%20denote%20blocks%20of%2016%20bits%20where%20all%20the%20bits%20are%20zeros.%20It%20may%20occur%20only%20once%20in%20the%20address%20to%20avoid%20ambiguity\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Header Structure\",\"lhsI\":\"%3Ca%20href%3D%22http%3A//dotw.wikia.com/wiki/IPv4%22%3Ehttp%3A//dotw.wikia.com/wiki/IPv4%3C/a%3E%3Cbr%20/%3E%20%3Cimg%20style%3D%22width%3A%20100%25%3B%20height%3A%20auto%3B%22%20src%3D%22../../wp-content/plugins/custom-qa/images/blobid1486809811176.jpg%22%20alt%3D%22%22%20/%3E\",\"rhsI\":\"https%3A//commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File%3AIPv6_header_rv1.png%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cimg%20style%3D%22width%3A%20100%25%3B%20height%3A%20auto%3B%22%20src%3D%22../../wp-content/plugins/custom-qa/images/blobid1486809917300.png%22%20alt%3D%22%22%20/%3E\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"Fragmentation%20of%20packets%20is%20allowed.%20Reassembly%20is%20done%20at%20the%20final%20destination%20of%20the%20packets\",\"rhsI\":\"Fragmentation%20is%20not%20allowed\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"Option%20field%20available\",\"rhsI\":\"Option%20field%20omitted%20for%20speed\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"The%20IPSec%20security%20protocol%20is%20optional%20for%20IPv4\",\"rhsI\":\"IPSec%20is%20mandatory%20for%20IPv6\"}]</p>\n', 'Answer for What is the difference between IPv4 &amp; IPv6?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'answer-for-what-is-the-difference-between-ipv4-ipv6', '', '', '2017-02-15 16:03:58', '2017-02-15 16:03:58', '', 3279, 'http://localhost/wp/dwqa-answer/answer-for-what-is-the-difference-between-ipv4-ipv6/', 0, 'dwqa-answer', '', 0),
