(3346, 25, '2017-02-17 14:27:14', '2017-02-17 14:27:14', '<p>[{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"Default%20Bearer%20is%20a%20term%20arose%20with%20the%20introduction%20of%20Evolved%20Packet%20Core%20and%20LTE.%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EIt%20represnts%20the%20EPS%20bearer%20which%20is%20first%20established%20for%20a%20new%20PDN%20connection%20and%20remains%20established%20throughout%20the%20lifetime%20of%20the%20PDN%20connection.\",\"rhsI\":\"Dedicated%26nbsp%3BBearer%20is%20a%20term%20arose%20with%20the%20introduction%20of%20Evolved%20Packet%20Core%20and%20got%20more%20fame%20with%20the%20VoLTE%20commercial%20deployments.%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EIt%20represents%20a%20context%20that%20is%20always%20linked%20to%20a%20default%20EPS%20bearer%20context%20and%20represents%20additional%20EPS%20bearer%20resources%20between%20the%20UE%20and%20the%20PDN.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Bitrate\",\"lhsI\":\"Default%20Bearer%20is%20characterized%20by%20Non-GBR%20%28Non%20Guaranteed%20Bitrate%29.\",\"rhsI\":\"Dedicated%20Bearer%20Can%20be%20either%20GBR%20%28Guaranteed%20Bitrate%29%20or%20Non-GBR%26nbsp%3B%28Non%20Guaranteed%20Bitrate%29.%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EThough%26nbsp%3Bthe%20GBR%20case%20is%20the%20most%20commercial%20deployed%20use%20case.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Use Case\",\"lhsI\":\"Default%20Bearer%20is%20commonly%20used%20for%20Internet%20Browsing%20and%20all%20Mobile%20Broadband%20services%20that%20don%27t%20require%20specific%20Quality%20of%20Service%20requirements.\",\"rhsI\":\"Dedicated%20Bearer%20is%20commonly%20used%20for%20Voice%20over%20LTE%20%28VoLTE%29%20and%20in%20theory%20to%20any%20service%20that%20require%20specific%20Quality%20of%20Service%20requirements.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Analogy to GPRS\",\"lhsI\":\"Default%20EPS%20Bearer%20can%20be%20analogised%20to%20the%20concept%20of%20Primary%26nbsp%3BPDP%20Context%20in%20PS%20Core/GPRS.\",\"rhsI\":\"Dedicated%26nbsp%3BEPS%20Bearer%20can%20be%20analogised%20to%20the%20concept%20of%20Secondary%20PDP%20Context%20in%20PS%20Core/GPRS.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"References\",\"lhsI\":\"3GPP%20TS%2023.401%26nbsp%3BLTE%3B%26nbsp%3BGeneral%20Packet%20Radio%20Service%20%28GPRS%29%20enhancements%20for%20Evolved%20Universal%20Terrestrial%20Radio%20Access%20Network%20%28E-UTRAN%29%20access%26nbsp%3B%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3E3GPP%20TS%2024.301%26nbsp%3BLTE%3B%26nbsp%3BNon-Access-Stratum%20%28NAS%29%26nbsp%3Bprotocol%20for%20Evolved%20Packet%20System%20%28EPS%29\",\"rhsI\":\"\"}]</p>\n', 'Answer for What is the difference between Default Bearer &amp; Dedicated Bearer?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'answer-for-what-is-the-difference-between-default-bearer-dedicated-bearer', '', '', '2017-02-17 14:28:21', '2017-02-17 14:28:21', '', 3342, 'http://localhost/wp/dwqa-answer/answer-for-what-is-the-difference-between-default-bearer-dedicated-bearer/', 0, 'dwqa-answer', '', 0),
(3347, 34, '2017-02-17 15:01:38', '2017-02-17 15:01:38', '<p>[{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"In%20near%20sighted%26nbsp%3Bindividuals%20which%20is%20also%20medically%20termed%20%22myopia%22%26nbsp%3B%2C%20a%20person%20is%20not%20able%20to%20see%20distant%20objects%20clearly.%20The%20light%20from%20objects%20that%20would%20normally%20be%20focused%20on%20the%20retina%20directly%2C%20instead%20is%20focused%26nbsp%3Bin%20front%20it.%20The%20retina%20is%20the%20light%20sensitive%20area%20which%20lies%20in%20the%20back%20of%20the%20eye%29.\",\"rhsI\":\"%3Cspan%20style%3D%22font-family%3A%20Lato%2C%20sans-serif%3B%20font-size%3A%200.8em%3B%22%3EIn%20long%20sighted%20individuals%20which%20is%20also%20medically%20termed%20%22hypermetropia%22%2C%26nbsp%3Ba%20person%20is%20not%20able%20to%20clearly%20see%20the%20nearby%20objects.%2C%20the%20light%20from%20objects%20that%20would%20normally%20be%20focused%20on%20the%20retina%20directly%2C%20instead%20is%20focused%20behind%26nbsp%3Bit.%3C/span%3E\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Illustrative diagram\",\"lhsI\":\"%3Cimg%20style%3D%22width%3A%20100%25%3B%20height%3A%20auto%3B%22%20src%3D%22../../wp-content/plugins/custom-qa/images/blobid1487345932150.png%22%20alt%3D%22%22%20/%3E\",\"rhsI\":\"%3Cimg%20style%3D%22width%3A%20100%25%3B%20height%3A%20auto%3B%22%20src%3D%22../../wp-content/plugins/custom-qa/images/blobid1487346016928.png%22%20alt%3D%22%22%20/%3E\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"causes\",\"lhsI\":\"Your%26nbsp%3Beyeball%20is%20longer%20than%20normal%2C%20your%26nbsp%3Bcornea%20and/or%20lens%20being%20too%20curved%20for%20the%20length%20of%20the%20eyeball.\",\"rhsI\":\"%3Cspan%20style%3D%22font-family%3A%20Lato%2C%20sans-serif%3B%20font-size%3A%200.8em%3B%22%3EYour%20eye%20is%20shorter%20than%20normal%2C%20your%20cornea%20is%20not%20curved%20enough%2C%20or%20your%20eye%20lens%20sits%20farther%20back%20in%20the%20eye%20than%20it%20should.%3C/span%3E\"},{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"Treatment\",\"lhsI\":\"