(3379, 22, '2017-02-21 04:11:06', '2017-02-21 04:11:06', '<p>[{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"Introduction\",\"lhsI\":\"Private%20Cloud%20and%20Public%20Cloud%20represent%20two%20different%20Deployment%20Models%20of%20Cloud%20Computing%20according%20to%20NIST%20%28National%20Institute%20of%20Standards%20and%20Technology%29%20definition.%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EThere%20are%20two%20other%20deployment%20models%20explained%20by%20NIST%20in%20the%20same%20publication%3B%20namely%2C%20Community%20Cloud%20and%20Hybrid%20Cloud.\",\"rhsI\":\"\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"The%20cloud%20infrastructure%20is%20provisioned%20for%20open%20use%20by%20the%20general%20public.%20It%20may%20be%20owned%2C%20managed%2C%20and%20operated%20by%20a%20business%2C%20academic%2C%20or%20government%20organization%2C%20or%20some%20combination%20of%20them.%20It%20exists%20on%20the%20premises%20of%20the%20cloud%20provider.\",\"rhsI\":\"The%20cloud%20infrastructure%20is%20provisioned%20for%20exclusive%20use%20by%20a%20single%20organization%20comprising%20multiple%20consumers%20%28e.g.%2C%20business%20units%29.%20It%20may%20be%20owned%2C%20managed%2C%20and%20operated%20by%20the%20organization%2C%20a%20third%20party%2C%20or%20some%20combination%20of%20them%2C%20and%20it%20may%20exist%20on%20or%20off%20premises.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Examples of providers\",\"lhsI\":\"Example%20of%20mega%20scale%20Public%20Cloud%20service%20providers%20are%3A%3Cbr%20/%3E%0A%3Cul%3E%0A%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A//aws.amazon.com/%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22font-family%3A%20Lato%2C%20sans-serif%3B%22%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22font-size%3A%2012.8px%3B%22%3EAmazon%20Web%20Services%20%28AWS%29%3C/span%3E%3C/span%3E%3C/a%3E%3C/li%3E%0A%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%22https%3A//cloud.google.com/%22%20target%3D%22_blank%22%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22font-family%3A%20Lato%2C%20sans-serif%3B%22%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22font-size%3A%2012.8px%3B%22%3EGoogle%20Cloud%20Platform%3C/span%3E%3