(3471, 32, '2017-03-04 19:09:05', '2017-03-04 19:09:05', '[{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"For%20the%20Americans%20the%20Sport%20that%20Messi%20and%20Ronaldo%20play%20is%20called%20Soccer%2C%20this%20is%20the%20sport%20all%20the%20World%20calls%20Football%20%28except%20the%20USA%20and%20maybe%20Canada%29.\",\"rhsI\":\"On%20the%20other%20hand%20the%20sport%20in%20which%202%20teams%20play%20on%20a%20rectangular%20field%20wearing%20helmets%20with%20goalposts%20at%20each%20end%20is%20called%20Football%20by%20Americans%20and%20American%20Football%20by%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.\"}]', 'Answer for What is the difference between Soccer &amp; Football?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'answer-for-what-is-the-difference-between-soccer-football', '', '', '2017-03-04 19:09:05', '2017-03-04 19:09:05', '', 3436, 'http://localhost/wp/dwqa-answer/answer-for-what-is-the-difference-between-soccer-football/', 0, 'dwqa-answer', '', 0),
(3472, 14, '2017-03-05 05:36:23', '2017-03-05 05:36:23', '<p>[{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"Protocol Stack\",\"lhsI\":\"%3Cimg%20style%3D%22width%3A%20100%25%3B%20height%3A%20auto%3B%22%20src%3D%22../../wp-content/plugins/custom-qa/images/image_1489684319.png%22%20alt%3D%22%22%20/%3E\",\"rhsI\":\"\"},{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"Type Of signaling\",\"lhsI\":\"SS7%20and%20Diameter%20are%20signaling%20protocols%20used%20to%20exchange%20signaling%20messages%20between%20network%20elements%20.%20Both%20can%20be%20considered%20as%20out%20of%20band%20signaling%20%2C%20where%20signaling%20layer%20is%20completely%20independent%20of%20the%20traffic%28forward%20plane%29%20.%20This%20is%20a%20major%20advantage%20for%20signaling%20expansion%20and%20scalability\",\"rhsI\":\"\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"SS7%20is%20the%20signaling%20System%20No.7%20which%20is%20the%20replacement%20of%20SS5%20and%20SS6%20.%20SS7%20is%20mainly%20used%20for%20digital%20commuinication%20signaling%20%28e.g.%20Voice%2C%20Mobility%20and%20VAS%20%29\",\"rhsI\":\"Diameter%20is%20initially%20used%20for%20Authentication%2C%20authorization%2C%20and%20accounting%20%28AAA%29%20protocol%20.The%20name%20driven%20as%20a%20play%20on%20words%20of%20RADIUS%20protocol%20which%20had%20many%20limitations%20.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"History\",\"lhsI\":\"SS7%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20successful%20signaling%20protocols%20have%20been%20ever%20developed%20.True%20it%20has%20many%20limitations%20and%20security%20threats%20%2C%20yet%20it%27s%20deployed%20since%201980%20until%20the%20moment%20%21%20SS5%20was%20in%20band%20signaling%20protocol%20which%20is%20very%20in-flexible%20%2C%20So%20in%201977%20ITU-T%20released%20SS6%20as%20the%20first%20out%20of%20band%20Common%20Channel%20Signaling%20%28CCS%29%20protocol%20.%20However%20%2C%20SS6%20didn%27t%20succeed%20as%20it%20was%26nbsp%3Brestricted%20to%2028-bit%20signal%20unit%20which%20is%20not%20suitable%20for%20Digital%20commuinication%20systems%20.\",\"rhsI\":\"RADIUS%20was%20the%20dominant%20AAA%20protocol%20since%20developed%20by%20Livingston%20Enterprises%20as%20a%20reply%20to%20Merit%20Network%20RFI%20in%201991%20.In%20order%20to%20solve%20RADIUS%20limitations%28reliability%2C%20scalability%2C%20security%20and%20flexibility%29%20%2C%26nbsp%3BP.%20Calhoun%2C%20G.%20Zorn%2C%20and%20P.%20Pan%20in%201998%20released%20Diameter%20protocol%20which%20can%26nbsp%3Bdefine%20a%20policy%20protocol%20.which%20allow%20a%20single%20server%20to%20handle%20policies%20%2CAAA%2C%20and%20resource%20control%20for%20many%20services.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Identifiers\",\"lhsI\":\"%3Cul%3E%0A%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ESignaling%20Point%20code%20%28SPC%29%20%3Cspan%20style%3D%22font-family%3A%20Lato%2C%20sans-serif%3B%20font-size%3A%200.8em%3B%22%3E%2C%3C/span%3E%3C/strong%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22font-family%3A%20Lato%2C%20sans-serif%3B%20font-size%3A%200.8em%3B%22%3E%26nbsp%3B%3C/span%3E%3C/li%3E%0A%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22font-family%3A%20Lato%2C%20sans-serif%3B%20font-size%3A%200.8em%3B%22%3EUnique%20per%20each%20node%20in%20the%20SS%26amp%3B%20network%20format%20identified%20by%20ITU%20%28values%200-3%29%20as%20NI-SPC.%20The%20SPC%20part%20is%2014%20bits%20wide%20and%20already%20written%20in%20decimal%20format.%3C/span%3E%3C/li%3E%0A%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EGlobal%20Title%20Address%28GT%29%26nbsp%3B%3C/strong%3E%3C/li%3E%0A%3C/ul%3E%0A%3Col%3E%0A%3Cli%3EE.164%28MSISDN%29%20%3D%20CC+NDC+SN%20-%20%28%20Country%20Code+National%20Destination%20Code+Subscriber%20Number%29%20e.g.%2091-98-71405178%3C/li%3E%0A%3C/ol%3E%0A%3Col%3E%0A%3Cli%3EE.212%28IMSI%29%20%3D%20MCC+MNC+MSIN%20-%20%28Mobile%20Country%20Code+Mobile%20Network%20Code+Mobile%20Subscription%20Identification%20Number%29%20e.g.%20404-68-6600620186%20%28MTNL%20delhi%29%20-%3C/li%3E%0A%3Cli%3EE.214%28MGT%29%20%3D%20combination%20of%20E.212%20and%20E.164%28CC+NDC+MSIN%29%20%28Exact%20combination%20is%20defined%20in%20the%20operators%20IR21%20document%29%3C/li%3E%0A%