(3503, 25, '2017-03-13 17:41:04', '2017-03-13 17:41:04', '<p>[{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"Concept\",\"lhsI\":\"The%20term%20Bearer%20is%20very%20common%20to%20use%20in%20Mobile%20Networks%20ecosystem.%20Bearer%20in%20English%20is%20the%20messenger%20or%20the%20thing/person%20who%20holds%20something.%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EThis%20is%20why%20the%20word%20%26ldquo%3BBearer%26rdquo%3B%20is%20not%20commonly%20used%20solely%20in%20Mobile%20Networks.%20It%20is%20always%20adjacent%20to%20another%20word%20that%20defines%20the%20nature%20of%20this%20bearer%3F%20What%20does%20it%20carry%3F%20What%20are%20the%20end%20points%3F%20etc.%26nbsp%3B%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EAn%20example%20of%20these%20%26ldquo%3Bbearer%26rdquo%3B%20terms%3B%20S1%20Bearer%2C%20EPS%20Bearer%2C%20Radio%20Bearer%2C%20Radio%20Access%20Bearer%2C%20E-Radio%20Access%20Bearer%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EAlthough%20Bearer%20can%20carry%20Signalling%20such%20as%20SRB%20%28Signalling%20Radio%20Bearer%29.%20However%2C%20Bearers%20are%20commonly%20discussed%20as%20Service%20Bearers%20carrying%20User%20Plane.\",\"rhsI\":\"\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"Radio%20Bearer%20is%20the%20channel%20transporting%20the%20User%20Plane%20between%20UE%20and%20RNC%20in%203G%20and%20between%20UE%20and%20eNB%20in%20LTE.%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EAlthough%20Definition%20might%20be%20seen%20as%20not%20100%25%20accurate%20because%20Radio%20Bearer%20can%20carry%20Signaling%20traffic%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Signalling%20Radio%20Bearers.%20but%20the%20majority%20of%20professionals%20when%20they%20talk%20about%20Data%20Radio%20bearer%20%28DRB%29%2C%20they%20commonly%20refer%20to%20it%20with%20Radio%20Bearer.\",\"rhsI\":\"Radio%20Access%20Bearer%20is%20the%20logical%20bearer%20transporting%20User%20Plane%20between%20UE%20%26amp%3B%20SGSN%20in%20case%20of%20Non%20Direct%20Tunnel.%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EIt%20logically%20consists%20of%20the%20Bearer%20between%20UE%20%26amp%3B%20RNC%20%28RB%29%20and%20the%20Bearer%20between%2