(3509, 25, '2017-03-14 17:40:49', '2017-03-14 17:40:49', '<p>[{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"3GPP%20Access%20are%20the%20Radio%20Access%20technologies%20%28RATs%29%20specified%26nbsp%3Bby%203GPP.%26nbsp%3B%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EExample%20of%20these%20types%20are%20the%20GERAN%2C%20UTRAN%2C%20%26amp%3B%20LTE.\",\"rhsI\":\"Non-3GPP%20Access%20are%20the%20accesses%20that%20are%20not%20specified%20in%203GPP.%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3ENormally%203GPP%20standards%20defines%20how%20these%20technologies%20can%20be%26nbsp%3Binter-worked%20and%20integrated%20with%203GPP%20ecosystems.%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EExample%20of%20these%20technologies%20are%20WiFi%2C%20DSL%2C%20%26amp%3B%20WiMAx.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"Types\",\"lhsI\":\"As%20per%20TS%203GPP%2024.008%20R12%2C%20the%20below%20access%20types%20for%203GPP%20Access%20are%20noted%3Cbr%20/%3E%0A%3Cul%3E%0A%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EUTRAN%3C/strong%3E%20-%26nbsp%3BUniversal%20Terrestrial%20Radio%20Access%20Network%3C/li%3E%0A%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EGERAN%3C/strong%3E%20-%26nbsp%3BGSM%20EDGE%20Radio%20Access%20Network%3C/li%3E%0A%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EGAN%3C/strong%3E%20-%26nbsp%3BGeneric%20Access%20Network%3C/li%3E%0A%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EHSPA%20Evolution%20%28HSPA+%29%3C/strong%3E%20-%26nbsp%3BEvolved%20High%20Speed%20Packet%20Access%3C/li%3E%0A%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EEUTRAN%3C/strong%3E%20-%20Evolved%20Universal%20Mobile%20Telecommunications%20System%20%28UMTS%29%20Terrestrial%26nbsp%3B%3C/li%3E%0A%3C/ul%3E%0A%3Cbr%20/%3EFor%20Non-3GPP%20Access%2C%20the%20below%20RAT%20Type%20is%20noted%3Cbr%20/%3E%0A%3Cul%3E%0A%3Cli%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22font-family%3A%20Lato%2C%20sans-serif%3B%22%3E%3Cspan%20style%3D%22font-size%3A%2012.8px%3B%22%3E%26nbsp%3B%3C/span%3E%3C/span%3E%3Cstrong%3EWLAN%3C/strong%3E%20-%20Wireless%20LAN%3C/li%3E%0A%3C/ul%3E\",\"rhsI\":\"\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Categories\",\"lhsI\":\"No%20Significant%20categories%20exist%20for%203GPP%20Access%20except%20the%20types%20mentioned%20in%20the%20above%20point%20of%20comparison.\",\"rhsI\":\"Non%203GPP%20Access%20can%20be%20classified%20into%20two%20main%20categories.%3Cbr%20/%3E%0A%3Cul%3E%0A%3Cli%3ETrusted%20non-3GPP%20Access%20-%20It%20is%20a%20case%20where%20the%20access%20can%20be%20integrated%20directly/transparently%20with%20the%20mobile%20core%20without%20significant%20security%20considerations.%3C/li%3E%0A%3Cli%3ENon-trusted%20non-3GPP%20Access%20-%20It%20is%20the%20case%20where%20security%20measures%20is%20needed%20to%20have%20a%20secure%20connection%20%28Commonly%20IPSec%29%20between%20the%20access%20and%20the%20Mobile%20Core.%26nbsp%3B%3C/li%3E%0A%3C/ul%3E%0ANote%20-%20The%20decision%20of%26nbsp%3Bwhich%20non-3GPP%20technologies%20should%20be%20considered%20trusted%20or%20untrusted%26nbsp%3Bis%20operator%20specific%20and%20not%20specified%20by%203GPP.\"}]</p>\n', 'Answer for What is the difference between 3GPP Access &amp; Non 3GPP Access?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'answer-for-what-is-the-difference-between-3gpp-access-non-3gpp-access', '', '', '2017-03-14 17:47:46', '2017-03-14 17:47:46', '', 3507, 'http://localhost/wp/dwqa-answer/answer-for-what-is-the-difference-between-3gpp-access-non-3gpp-access/', 0, 'dwqa-answer', '', 0),
(3510, 58, '2017-03-15 03:29:50', '2017-03-15 03:29:50', '[{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"In%202010%2C%20the%20industry%20realized%20that%20they%20can%20produce%20new%20innovative%20solutions%20to%20consumers%20by%20relying%20on%20the%20cellular%20communication%20between%20devices%2C%20and%20this%20was%20one%20of%20the%20initial%20differentiation%20points%20between%20IoT%20and%20M2M.%20In%20more%20details%2C%20if%20the%20communication%20is%20directly%20impacting%20the%20consumer%20experience%2C%20then%20it%27s%20IoT.%20If%20the%20communication%20is%20NOT%20directly%20impacting%20a%20specific%20consumer%2C%20then%20it%27s%20M2M.\",\"rhsI\":\"M2M%20refers%20to%20Machine-To-Machine%20communication%20which%20used%20to%20exist%20many%20years%20ago.%20In%20the%20Mid%201970%27s%20M2M%20was%20used%20to%20carry%20information%20about%20remote%20systems%20to%20the%20main%20observation%20and%20operation%20centers%20via%20long%20running%20cables.%26nbsp%3B%3Cbr%20\\/%3EAn%20example%20of%20the%20early%20M2M%20communication%20was%20the%20communication%20between%20the%20huge%20oil%20drilling%20machines%20and%20the%20nearby%20control%20%26amp%3B%20operation%20centers%20which%20are%20monitoring%20all%20the%20information%20about%20temperature%2C%20pressure%2C%20and%20all%20sorts%20of%20attributes%20from%20the%20drilling%20head.%3Cbr%20\\/%3E%3Cbr%20\\/%3E%3Cbr%20\\/%3E\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"For%20example%2C%20a%20leading%20GPS%20company%20in%20Europe%2C%20relied%20on%20M2M%20communication%20to%20capture%20the%20traffic%20density%20on%20streets%2C%20and%20re-sell%20this%20information%20to%20customers.%20Although%20this%20solution%20had%20an%20impact%20on%20customer%20experience%2C%20at%20that%20time%20it%20was%20still%20referred%20to%20as%20M2M%20because%20the%20enterprise%20selling%20this%20entity%20didn%27t%20expose%20this%20communication%2C%20and%20the%20IoT%20term%20was%20not%20yet%20invented%20at%20that%20time.\",\"rhsI\":\"A%20key%20point%20in%20distinguishing%20M2M%20communication%20from%20traditional%20control%20units%20within%20systems%20was%20the%20definition%20of%20the%20system%20itself%2C%20which%20eventually%20boils%20down%20to%20whether%20the%20system%20can%20operate%20without%20the%20communication%20system%20or%20not.%20If%20system%20A%20can%20fully%20operate%20without%20System%20B%2C%20then%20the%20communication%20between%20both%20systems%20is%20M2M.%20If%20system%20A%20can%27t%20operate%20without%20System%20B%2C%20then%20System%20B%20is%20the%20control%20unit%20for%20system%20A%2C%20and%20this%20communication%20is%20NoT%20M2M.%3Cbr%20\\/%3E\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"%26nbsp%3BThis%20differentiation%20%28about%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20communication%29%20was%20changed%20few%20years%20later%20when%20more%20smart%20devices%20became%20visible%20and%20popular.%20The%20term%20IoT%20started%20to%20refer%20to%20communication%20between%20multiple%20devices%20from%20the%20same%20manufacturers%20communicating%20with%20each%20other%2C%20to%20serve%20a%20single%20customer.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20communication%20between%20a%20customer%27s%20smart%20watch%20and%20the%20his%20house%20held%20Air%20Condition%20unit%20to%20adjust%20the%20room%20temperature%20when%20the%20customer%20is%20approaching%20his%20house.\",\"rhsI\":\"In%20around%202007%20the%20term%20M2M%20became%20more%20popular%20in%20the%20industry%20and%20started%20to%20be%20associated%20with%20machines%20communicating%20over%20cellular%20connection%20%282G\\/3G%20and%204G%29.%3Cbr%20\\/%3EAt%20this%20stage%2C%20this%20communication%20was%20mainly%20for%20industry%20control%20and%20process%20enhancements.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"This%20definition%20was%20changed%20again%20recently%20with%20the%20introduction%20of%20Internet%20of%20Everything%20%28IoE%29%20which%20started%20to%20refer%20to%20communication%20between%20devices%20from%20different%20manufacturers%20which%20rely%20on%20a%20specific%20framework%20to%20communicate%20and%20exchange%20data%20a%20bit%20more%20openly%2C%20although%20this%20is%20still%20in%20early%20stages%2C%20and%20the%20business%20model%20for%20this%20communication%20is%20not%20utilized%20to%20a%20good%20extent%20yet.\",\"rhsI\":\"\"}]', 'Answer for What is the difference between IoT &amp; M2M?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'answer-for-what-is-the-difference-between-iot-m2m', '', '', '2017-03-15 03:29:50', '2017-03-15 03:29:50', '', 3303, 'http://localhost/wp/dwqa-answer/answer-for-what-is-the-difference-between-iot-m2m/', 0, 'dwqa-answer', '', 0),
