(3518, 56, '2017-03-17 14:24:34', '2017-03-17 14:24:34', '[{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"is%20a%20psychobiologic%20syndrome%20associated%20with%20impaired%20control%20over%20a%20drug%20%28i.e.%20compulsive%20use%20despite%20harmful%20consequences%29.%20it%20appears%20to%20be%20influenced%20by%20genetic%2C%20social%20and%20environmental%20factors.%26nbsp%3B\",\"rhsI\":\"is%20a%20biological%20adaptation%20of%20the%20body%20to%20long%20term%20usage%20of%20a%20drug%2C%20such%20that%20abrupt%20cessation%20can%20lead%20to%20serious%20withdrawal%20%28abstinence%29%20symptoms.%20these%20symptoms%20may%20include%20increase%20in%20the%20heart%20rate%20and\\/or%20blood%20pressure%2C%20sweating%20and%20tremors%20%28shakes%29.%20this%20phenomenon%20is%20the%20same%20whether%20the%20drug%20is%20used%20for%20medical%20purposes%20%28e.g.%20morphine%20for%20cancer%20pain%29%2C%20or%20used%20illicitly%20%28e.g.%20heroin%29.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"What are the dangers?\",\"lhsI\":\"Addiction%20may%20cause%20people%20to%20act%20irrationally%20when%20they%20don%27t%20have%20the%20drug%20they%20are%20addicted%20to%2C%20and%20in%20severe%20cases%20the%20addiction%20thoughts%20can%20transform%20the%20drug%20of%20choice%20into%20their%20central%20focus%20of%20life.\",\"rhsI\":\"The%20symptoms%20of%20withdrawal%20could%20be%20life%20threatening%20and%20may%20lead%20to%20death%2C%20e.g.%20arrhythmia%20%28disturbances%20in%20heart%20beats%29%2C%20and%20severe%20dehydration%20and%20convulsions%20%28fits%29.%20%26nbsp%3B\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"How to treat?\",\"lhsI\":\"Rehabilitation%20programs%20in%20a%20mental%20facility%20to%20teach%20the%20addicts%20how%20to%20handle%20the%20inevitable%20temptation%20to%20relapse%2C%20in%20the%20form%20of%20education%20sessions%2C%20relapse%20prevention%20plans%20and%20coping%20techniques.%26nbsp%3B\",\"rhsI\":\"%281%29%20Detoxification%20programs%2C%20that%20may%20last%20anywhere%20from%20a%20few%20days%20to%20a%20f