(3534, 14, '2017-03-24 06:11:33', '2017-03-24 06:11:33', '[{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"Important Concept\",\"lhsI\":\"It%27s%20important%20to%20understand%20first%20the%20%22Time%20Value%20of%20money%22%20concept%20.This%20simply%20reflect%20the%20depreciation%20of%20money%20value%20across%20time%20.%20The%20%241000%20you%20have%20today%20worth%20more%20than%20%241000%20you%20have%20month%20after%20%2C%20due%20to%20inflation%20and%20other%20finaical%20impacts%20.%20Assume%20cash%20flow%20of%20three%20years%20in%20the%20future%20for%20the%20%241000%20with%20a%207%25%20discount%20rate.%20The%20present%20value%20of%20that%20cash%20flow%20is%3A%20%241%2C000%20/%20%281%20+%20.07%29%5E3%20%3D%20%24816.3%20.\",\"rhsI\":\"\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Type\",\"lhsI\":\"A%20financial%20performance%20measure\",\"rhsI\":\"An%20investment%20valuation%20method\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Purpose\",\"lhsI\":\"Used%20by%20companies%20to%20pursue%20opportunities%20that%20enhance%20shareholder%20value.\",\"rhsI\":\"Used%20by%20investors%20to%20estimate%20the%20attractiveness%20of%20an%20investment%20opportunity\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"Free%20cash%20flow%20%28FCF%29%20represents%20the%20cash%20that%20a%20company%20is%20able%20to%20generate%20after%20spending%20the%20money%20required%20to%20maintain%20or%20expand%20its%20asset%20base.%20A%20company%20that%20has%20positive%20FCF%20means%20it%20makes%20more%20money%20than%20it%20is%20spending%20.\",\"rhsI\":\"Discounted%20Cash%20Flow%20%28DCF%29%20is%20the%20future%20free%20cash%20flow%20projections%20for%20a%20certain%20company%20discounted%20to%20arrive%20at%20a%20present%20value%20estimate%20.%20So%20simply%20investors%20studying%20performance%20of%20a%20certain%20company%20%2Chave%20to%20estimate%20how%20much%20FCF%20this%20company%20will%20generate%20for%20the%20future%20years%20%2C%20then%20discount%20those%20values%20to%20get%20the%20current%20value%20of%20these%20future%20incomes%20.%20The